Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 110, 37. Name Damothemis. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0115.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0854)
